< Rating>
5< /Rating>
< Text>
Exceptionally great food, friendly service, and lovely food presentation! Impressed with new ownership and subtle changes that make it unique to Betty's. We're previous loyal patrons of George's but are certainly happy to have Betty in town. Fresh tasty hummus pairs well with an aromatic Perisan salad over thin bread. I enjoyed a hearty plate of lentil soup which I devoured as my main dish. Spouse ordered the combo plate with chicken and beef kabobs that he thoroughly enjoyed. Servings sizes are generous, bring your appetite, or even share with a friend. Our server was charming, efficient (water glasses ALWAYS filled), and had a nice sense of humor. We are big Fans of Betty's and would highly recommend to anyone looking for a great meal in town!< /Text>

<Time>1613456571479<//Time><rating>5</rating>< text>
Welll, let me start off by saying I absolutely love quality, let me repeat, quality Persian food. I have traveled hours to go to the Bay or Sac to get something decent. We stumbled on this place looking for something that wasn't packed due to it being Valentine's day and all. Ok let me also mention I‚Äôm Middle Eastern myself and KNOW good quality ethnic food.
We called to see if they are open for dine in and the woman who answered the phone was so so pleasant. Very welcoming. So we get there, nice family owned restaurant. Very quaint. The beautiful Persian music was playing. We ordered our food and sat down to eat. I have no words to describe how happy I am to FINALLY have a GREAT Persian restaurant close enough to frequent regularly. The food was superb. The kubede kabab was amazing. My husband ordered the steak and chicken kabob combo. Holy smokes. I was blown away. We ordered two more dishes to go for dinner.  I want to try everything on the menu. Oh and how can I forget to mention the Baklava!!!! YUMMMM. I had to write this review quickly so people can spread the word. Lets support this amazing spot.</text>

Earlier today I told my wife that I was craving Kabobs and I really wanted to feast but didn't want to spend a bunch of money at a sit down nor did I want to fire up the grill and go through that hassle of making kabobs. A couple weeks back we passed Betty's after church but I was in a rush to get home but the smell of the Kabobs were stuck in my head since then. I called them up today and a lovely lady picked up the phone and I ordered 2 koobideh dinner plates, a skewer of tomatos, 5 skewers of koobideh and 1 skewer of chicken breasts. Let me tell you they like to add roasted jalapenos on the side for free which was an awesome bonus. All of this for less than $60!!!!! I gave them $60 and an extra $10 as tip. This much food would be well over $100 anywhere else. The owners were extremely hospitable and accommodating. I told them I would be cutting it close to their closing time and they said no worries and they waited for me. I don't think I'll ever make Kabobs at home anymore. I'll be using Betty's from now on for all my events. This is a must go to for Keto meats.< /Text><gmap_id>0x809056c7cb8d6983:0x432875af1b9a0224<//gmap_id><Name>Eilo Betoushana< /Name>< Response>

< Text>
I woke up on a Saturday to my cat clearly in pain. I had just moved to Pine Grove and hadn't established a vet yet. I tried to call the vet an hour before they opened and someone answered! An hour early on a Saturday morning i was able to get him in right as they opened.  It was an emergency so i was expecting emergency prices for the visit.  My cat had an abscess that was early enough to just keep clean. They gave him all the shots he needed with the visit.  The vet and staff took care of my cat like he was their own. I was in and out for way less than i would have ever dreamed.  I had to make sure they were charging me for the emergency visit and routine shots he needed. This will be my vet for life! Thank you!</Text>

<user_name>Stacey Fernandez<//user_name>< review>
I purchased a car from this location at the end of December.  The service was amazing and I would refer people to visit here to purchase a car.  I got the payment I wanted and the down payment I needed.  My disappointment comes from the condition of the car.  Which I take responsibility for not checking in more detail.
1. Within 24 hours I found the one of my passenger window will not roll down from the button on the door, but I can control it from my door (the lock is not on)
2. One of the third row seatbelts does not buckle, so I can not put my child back there like I had hoped.
3. Numerous vent and plastic covers are broken and off and I can not get them to stay on.
4. Stains on my ceiling
5. About two weeks after I purchased I am notified that the air bag is not working.

Now I understand that I signed an "as is" contract, but I feel that there was a lack of pride in the product that was sold.  Why was the car on the lot to sell if not in working order? Makes me wonder what else wasn't checked....  The lesson for me is now when I buy a car I will roll down every single window, check all seat belts even if I have to crawl in the third row and check all plastic covers.
God only knows what it will cost to fix the window, seat belt and air bag but it sucks that I have to fix them before I made my first payment....<//review>

<review>This was a pretty easy transaction. I have poor credit after a divorce and really wanted to buckle down and get my stuff together. I applied online, they said I was approved. Went in and met with Henry. He helped get the process started. We walked the lot and we talked about what I could get and what I couldn't. Met with Jason, finance, who really is helpful and transparent about my situation. I am in sales also, so I am very leery of other sales people. (I know I know) It was almost painless. LOL! I feel I got a fair deal for what my situation is. The customer service is very good here. Henry and Jason were always available to answer my questions if I was there in person, phone, or via text. I started this process on the computer. I went down for the initial meeting which was about 90 minutes, which resulted in my picking a car, and working the numbers. I had a list of things that I did want. It's always the little things that matter. Like the SD card for navigation, floor mats, warranty, washed and detailed when I pick up please. Oh and my payment needs to be here. Once that was all squared away and we had a deal we were all happy with, I came back the next day and closed paperwork with Juan. WHo was also very nice and answered all of my questions. I am gonna give them 5 stars because they really wanted to work with me. My only two suggestions... Owners manuals for the cars are a MUST! I was disappointed when mine did not have one. And the gas tank should be filled up before the customer leaves the lot. Because I had to stop for gas on the way home and had to You Tube where the gas lever for the gas tank was to get it open. Little things guys! All in all very satisfied.<//review>< Pictures>

**** Update: so while we were at this office they told us that they couldn't get us a loan for a truck with a payment less than $700 a month for a used truck , which was way over our budget and that the loan would be at 20% or more. Update- I still think that this place is the best place to get a car if your credit isn't so good. I love my car. I only have one small complaint. It's been over two months and I still have not received my permanent license plates from the DMV. I called the DMV and they told me the dealer hasn't turned in the final paperwork yet. So I contacted Paul Blanco, and a girl returned my call and said that I needed to bring the vehicle in so to get could verify the VIN #. SO, I drove all the way from Victorville to Norco to take the car in for the verification. I was in and out in about 10 min. Great right? Wrong! In less than a week later, I received ANOTHER call for me to bring the car in to verify the VIN #!!! I told the person on the phone to that I already did that, and that was only 5 days previous!  I realize that to these people probably sell hundreds if not thousands of cars a day, they get busy. Anyway, if you buy a vehicle from this company, stay on top of things when it comes to getting your plates, tags, etc. They are very slow in turning in their paperwork and they are not through in this area. <Time>1464777970842</Time><Rating>1<//Rating><review>By far the worst experiences I've ever had anywhere. Please consider my review if you're looking to buy here

Let me just say, i live at the northern most part of fontana. Paul blancos is a 40 minute drive on a good day. Bad day, the drive ends up being between and hour to 2 hrs.

Day 1-Sunday. I walk in around 10 am and within a few moments, Henry Smith, salesman, comes out of the offices to greet me in the lobby. We run all my documents and I find out I've been denied. No surprise there. So they ask for a cosigner to which I have one. So we run the information and after about 5 minutes of me waiting, someone else approaches me (short, older Hispanic male) and tells me that he has 2 lenders who may be willing to work with me. However, according to him, neither of the representatives are near a computer. At this point, it's 1 pm and I have to leave for work so both Henry and the older Hispanic male tell me they will give me a call by 6pm that night or by the next morning. 530pm hits and I haven't heard anything so I call them, leave a voice mail with my name and number and ask for a call back at THEIR earliest convenience.

DAY 2. MONDAY. Around 11 am, I call, get no answer and leave another message. I text Henry, the first salesman to begin my case, and he tells me just to go in. I respond by telling him that i would rather know beforehand as to whether or not I had been approved. He tells me he could go in the next day if I would be willing to wait. I tell him I can be at the dealer at 130.

DAY 3. TUESDAY. I get a text from Henry at 11 am. The text read " you are approved"  so 130 hits and I find myself in the lobby at Paul Blanco. I end up waiting a little more than 2 hours, the entire time, a few salesmen cracking jokes and speaking about me as if I weren't there.  Finally, Herbert comes up and tells me that Henry wasn't there and hadn't even notified them that I was going. If fact, it didn't seem like he even had any intention of him going in to help me. Herbert looks at my application and then tells me that I was approved but the ONLY way I would be able to leave with a car would be if my cosigner were to trade in one of HIS current cars. I told Herbert that Henry NEVER mentioned that to me not even when I applied a few days before. I asked to speak to the manager and the only thing me manager did was give me a number for a complaints department.

All in all, I drove a total of 2.5 hours there and back, wasted 2 hours waiting around, and then left without a car because of something that Henry never mentioned at all in the days that we had been texting. I would definitely never recommend coming here since the only helpful one was the receptionist. This place is a waste of time, energy, and gas..<//review><pictures>None< /pictures><resp>None<//resp><gmapID>0x80dcb0f1a98a65cd:0x4a7861bbe8dd2551</gmapID></record>
